[There are three sources of prime importance: firstly Boniface’s autograph rough draft (α) ; secondly (131) ΕΑΕ (p. 210) ; and thirdly Essv (132). The two last, from their close connexion, may be jointly designated as β. The letter from Zasius to Boniface (16 March : Basle MS. G. ΙΙ. 32. 17 ; ZE. 22), which is quoted at the end (γ), shows that Boniface sent him a copy of α, and in deference to his criticism omitted the translations of the Greek which are shown in the critical notes. As β represents the letter actually sent and received, I have given preference to its readings: though retaining the spelling of a.

This letter was very likely sent with Ep. 1083. The news which Bonifaee gives, clearly indicates that he had not written to Erasmus since Ep. 1020.]
